{"type":"message","id":"8a0bec7f","parentId":"065c27ed","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:07:59.169Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The process is gone too. It seems like background processes are being killed when the exec tool returns. The media-crawler-mcp starts up fine (shows \"Uvicorn running\") but then the process exits.\n\nThis could be because when the exec tool finishes and returns, the background child process (python main.py) is also terminated on Windows.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The media-crawler-mcp uses FastMCP with uvicorn. When I run it in the background via the exec tool, it starts but then the Python process for the main.py script exits... but uvicorn itself should keep running as a server.\n\nWait - actually, looking at the log again: \"Uvicorn running on http://127.0.0.1:18080\" is printed by uvicorn, but then the process exits. The issue might be that the python main.py script itself doesn't block - it starts uvicorn in a thread or something, and then the main thread exits.\n\nLet me check how FastMCP/uvicorn is set up in main.py."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c5a8b40ce7464124a9bb0781","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\ADHD_agent\\media-crawler-mcp\\main.py","offset":140}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783652871220}}
{"type":"message","id":"7c26bc6e","parentId":"8a0bec7f","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:07:59.174Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_c5a8b40ce7464124a9bb0781","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"@mcp.tool()\nasync def crawl_detail(platform: str = config.PLATFORM, store_type: str = config.SAVE_DATA_OPTION, video_id: list = []) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Start the crawler for the media platform by video ID.\n\n        args:\n            platform (str): The media platform to crawl. You can choose from 'xhs', 'dy', 'ks', 'bili', 'wb', 'tieba', 'zhihu'.\n            store_type (str): The storage type for data. You can choose from 'db', 'sqlite', 'json', 'csv'.\n            video_id (list): The video ID or URL to crawl details for.\n    \"\"\"\n    global crawler\n    config.PLATFORM = platform\n    config.SAVE_DATA_OPTION = store_type\n    \n    set_config(crawler_type=\"detail\", platform=platform, video_id=video_id)\n\n    if store_type in [\"db\", \"sqlite\"]:          \n        try:\n            await db.init_db_table(store_type=store_type)\n            await db.init_db()\n        except Exception as e:\n            return f\"Error occurred: Database connection failed: {e}, Please check your database configuration or use another storage type.\"\n\n    try:\n        crawler = CrawlerFactory.create_crawler(platform=platform)\n        await crawler.start()\n        return \"success to crawl\"\n    except Exception as e:\n        return f\"Error occurred: {e}\"\n\n@mcp.tool()\nasync def crawl_creator(platform: str = config.PLATFORM, store_type: str = config.SAVE_DATA_OPTION, creator_id: list = []) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Start the crawler for the media platform by creator id.\n    \n        args:\n            platform (str): The media platform to crawl. You can choose from 'xhs', 'dy', 'ks', 'bili', 'wb', 'tieba', 'zhihu'.\n            store_type (str): The storage type for data. You can choose from 'db', 'sqlite', 'json', 'csv'.\n            creator_id (list): The creator ID to crawl.\n    \"\"\"\n    global crawler\n    config.PLATFORM = platform\n    config.SAVE_DATA_OPTION = store_type\n    \n    set_config(crawler_type=\"creator\", platform=platform, creator_id=creator_id)\n\n    if store_type in [\"db\", \"sqlite\"]:          \n        try:\n            await db.init_db_table(store_type=store_type)\n            await db.init_db()\n        except Exception as e:\n            return f\"Error occurred: Database connection failed: {e}, Please check your database configuration or use another storage type.\"\n\n    try:\n        crawler = CrawlerFactory.create_crawler(platform=platform)\n        await crawler.start()\n        return \"success to crawl\"\n    except Exception as e:\n        return f\"Error occurred: {e}\"\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    import sys\n    transport = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) > 1 else 'sse'\n    mcp.run(transport=transport)\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783652879173}}
