{"type":"message","id":"f7442f47","parentId":"b5d06e04","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:09:18.444Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the /sse endpoint works! It returned 200 OK when the script called it. The issue is that the SSE stream is returning data but the script is timing out while reading it. The session endpoint format might be different from what I expected. Let me check how the SSE endpoint works.\n\nLooking at the log: \"GET /sse HTTP/1.1\" 200 OK - it connected. But then the script timed out while reading. The issue might be that the SSE endpoint for this MCP server sends the session_id in a different format.\n\nLet me look at the MCP server code to understand how the SSE endpoint works"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ce9fcf6003a540efa768e3e7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cmd /c \"curl -s -N http://127.0.0.1:18080/sse 2>&1\" &","yieldMs":5000,"timeout":8}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783652952330}}
