{"type":"message","id":"609bc9f9","parentId":"586d1dd2","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:09:36.170Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the `&` character at the end of the command is causing a PowerShell parsing error. Let me use `Start-Job` or a different approach to test the SSE endpoint.\n\nActually, I realize the SSE endpoint IS working (200 OK from the log). The issue is that the Python script's `init_mcp()` function is timing out while reading from the SSE stream. This is because the SSE endpoint is a streaming endpoint - it keeps sending events and never closes. The `requests.get(..., stream=True)` should work, but it seems like it's timing out.\n\nWait, looking at the log more carefully:\n- `GET /sse HTTP/1.1\" 200 OK` - the SSE endpoint returned 200\n\n\n- The script's `init_mcp()` timed out after 10 seconds (default timeout) while reading the stream\n\nThe problem is likely that the SSE endpoint sends events immediately and then closes, but if it's keeping the connection open or sending keep-alive events, the script might be waiting indefinitely. I should try with a shorter timeout or handle the stream differently.\n\nActually, looking at the code again, the 10-second timeout on `requests.get()` is for the connection itself, not the response reading. The real issue is that the stream never terminates - it keeps sending data until the crawler finishes. I need to close the connection after extracting the session_id instead of waiting for the stream to end.\n\nLet me modify the script to read just the first event and then close the connection immediately"},{"type":"text","text":"SSE 连接已通（200 OK），问题是流一直不关闭导致超时。改脚本——读到 session_id 就立即关闭连接：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0892b60dba6049c3abb092bd","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\linkang\\.openclaw\\workspace\\xhs_push_media_crawler.py","oldText":"def init_mcp():\n    \"\"\"连接 SSE 获取 session_id\"\"\"\n    s = requests.Session()\n    r = s.get(f'{MCP_URL}/sse', stream=True, timeout=10)\n    session_id = None\n    endpoint = None\n    for line in r.iter_lines():\n        line = line.decode()\n        if line.startswith('data:'):\n            data = line[5:].strip()\n            if 'session_id' in data:\n                try:\n                    obj = json.loads(data)\n                    session_id = obj.get('session_id', '')\n                except:\n                    pass\n            elif data.startswith('/'):\n                endpoint = data.split('?session_id=')[0] if '?session_id=' in data else data\n    r.close()\n    if not endpoint or not session_id:\n        raise Exception(f'无法获取 session_id，endpoint={endpoint}, session_id={session_id}')\n    full_endpoint = f'{MCP_URL}{endpoint}'\n    return s, full_endpoint, session_id","newText":"def init_mcp():\n    \"\"\"连接 SSE 获取 session_id，读到就关闭\"\"\"\n    s = requests.Session()\n    r = s.get(f'{MCP_URL}/sse', stream=True, timeout=30)\n    session_id = None\n    endpoint = None\n    try:\n        for line in r.iter_lines(timeout=30):\n            line = line.decode()\n            if line.startswith('data:'):\n                data = line[5:].strip()\n                if 'session_id' in data:\n                    try:\n                        obj = json.loads(data)\n                        session_id = obj.get('session_id', '')\n                    except:\n                        pass\n                elif data.startswith('/') and 'session_id' in data:\n                    endpoint = data.split('?session_id=')[0] if '?session_id=' in data else data\n                if session_id and endpoint:\n                    break\n    finally:\n        r.close()\n    if not endpoint or not session_id:\n        raise Exception(f'无法获取 session_id，endpoint={endpoint}, session_id={session_id}')\n    full_endpoint = f'{MCP_URL}{endpoint}'\n    return s, full_endpoint, session_id"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"outp