{"type":"message","id":"d212aedf","parentId":"bc596d69","timestamp":"2026-07-10T03:09:41.627Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Also need to add stream=True for the POST requests since they might stream too. Let me check the call_mcp function. Actually, for POST requests, requests library by default doesn't stream, so it should be fine. But I need to make sure the timeout is reasonable for the tool call.\n\nActually wait - the SSE connection is a GET that streams, and the tool calls are POST requests. The issue was that the GET /sse was hanging. Now that we close immediately after getting the session_id, the POST calls should work normally.\n\nLet me try running it"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_406c0931c1ab4a66be086693","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"C:\\Python314\\python.exe C:\\Users\\linkang\\.openclaw\\workspace\\xhs_push_media_crawler.py 2>&1","yieldMs":200000,"timeout":240}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783652976186}}
